searchParameters.q: how much is cabbage patch doll worth

answerBox.snippet: Cabbage Patch Kid dolls vary in price depending on their condition, but the average doll can sell for $20 to $500, and many have sold for at least $100. The value of a doll can increase from hundreds of dollars to thousands if its original box, body, clothes, adoption papers, and birth certificate are intact.

peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Of course, if online isn't for you, then checking out your local antique stores, boutique toy stores, or pawn shops may be helpful. These kinds of stores will usually have experts who can appraise your doll and tell you whether it's worth selling. Needless to say, the world loves a Cabbage Patch Kid.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can you tell how old a cabbage patch doll is?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Cabbage Patch Kids were copyrighted in 1978 and 1982, but mass-market dolls were not sold until 1983. Each year Coleco, and then later companies changed the colour of the signature. This means you can figure out a doll's year of manufacture/sale by knowing the company that made it and then looking at their bum.
